{"company_id": 29103, "company_name": "ten.dev", "short_description": "A context gathering co-pilot for your software team.", "long_description": "Developers love good documentation, but it suffers from one fatal flaw; developers hate to write it. \r\n\r\nThe problem with inadequate documentation is that improving, maintaining, and understanding software becomes difficult. If the context isn't documented, the only way to understand it is by asking the original developer (if they're still employed) and hoping they remember!\r\n\r\nWe provide an inversion of the standard \u201cask questions on your code using an LLM\u201d and instead use an LLM to generate questions on your code to ask you!\r\n\r\nWe ask developers valuable questions about their code in their usual messaging channels. We store these question-answer pairs in a vector store and provide an interface to query back this knowledge anytime!\r\n\r\nAfter all, the purpose of docs is to answer the why and how of code, so why not just create your docs this way?", "batch": "S23", "status": "Active", "tags": ["Productivity", "Chatbot", "AI Assistant"], "location": "San Francisco", "country": "US", "year_founded": 2023, "num_founders": 3, "founders_names": ["Eoghan Mulcahy", "Liam Mulcahy", "Eoin Walsh"], "team_size": 3, "website": "https://ten.dev", "cb_url": "", "linkedin_url": "https://www.linkedin.com/company/ten-dev/"}
