{"company_id": 12261, "company_name": "Pronto", "short_description": "Ride-sharing for second-tier cities in Latin America.", "long_description": "PRONTO is the first RIDE-SHARING + DELIVERY platform for SECOND-TIER cities in LATAM. \r\n\r\nIn second-tier cities all transactions are paid with cash, this is why the Uber model doesn\u00b4t work (since they have to collect their revenue from commissions). We solved this by creating a subscription model where drivers pay a monthly recurring subscription of 59 to 99 USD depending on their monthly revenue. This also generates a higher LTV with low CAC as well as high engagement and fidelity ratios.\r\n\r\nTraction: Since our launch, we have achieved over 2,000,000 processed trips with more than 200,000 users, we bootstrapped until we achieved half a million trips and entered YC.\r\n\r\nMarket Size: There are over 14,000 second-tier cities in LATAM, with more than 500 million people without any access to ride-sharing or technology platforms at all.\r\n", "batch": "W19", "status": "Active", "tags": ["Latin America", "Transportation"], "location": "Mexico City, Mexico", "country": "MX", "year_founded": null, "num_founders": 3, "founders_names": ["Miguel Martinez Cano", "Nydia Cano", "Gabriel Cano Rodr\u00edguez"], "team_size": 62, "website": "http://www.tuprontomx.com/", "cb_url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/pronto-app", "linkedin_url": "https://www.linkedin.com/company/tupronto"}
{"company_id": 12256, "company_name": "Glide", "short_description": "Create the app your business needs, without coding.", "long_description": "Glide is a web-based app builder that allows non-programmers to quickly create powerful and beautiful apps by combining prebuilt components with a familiar spreadsheet model.\r\n\r\nApp development has barely changed in 30 years. Glide will bring app development out of the Dark Ages, making it web-based, collaborative, and fun. Think of Google Docs or Figma but for building apps.\r\n\r\nWe believe that almost all apps can be built 10-100x faster, with higher quality, by starting with the data model and generating a polished app from high-level components that users customize.\r\n\r\nOur mission is to make it easy and fun for anyone to build amazing apps without code. In ten years, we want the majority of apps worldwide to have been built with Glide.\r\n\r\nWe're four technical founders with expertise in native mobile frameworks, developer tools, and product design. We've worked together for 5-10 years, and were all early employees at Xamarin, a mobile developer tools startup acquired by Microsoft in 2016.", "batch": "W19", "status": "Active", "tags": ["No-code"], "location": "San Francisco", "country": "US", "year_founded": 2019, "num_founders": 3, "founders_names": ["Mark Probst", "David Siegel", "Jason Smith"], "team_size": 40, "website": "https://www.glideapps.com", "cb_url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/glide-apps", "linkedin_url": "https://www.linkedin.com/company/glideapps/mycompany/"}
